I. Introduction
A. Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Frozen Assets Cold Storage (Frozen Assets) facility located at 2635 South Western Avenue in Chicago, Illinois, for the reduction accidental releases of hazardous materials.  This Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases.  The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including:
- Frozen Assets policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
- Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
- Hazard Assessment;
- Prevention Program;
- Five-Year Accident History;
- Emergency Response Plan;
- Emergency Communications;
- Spill Reporting/Environmental Release Procedures;
- Planned changes to improve safety; and
- Management Program

II. Frozen Assets Policies to Protect Health, Environment, and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at Frozen Assets; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities.  Frozen Assets is committeed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment.  It is Frozen Asset's policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.

